definition.value: The tendency to ignore, remove, falsify, or reexplain evidence of lesbianism in history, academia, the news media, and other primary sources. Lesbians may also be ignored within the LGBTQIA+ community and their identity may not be acknowledged.
Equality of persons or groups in the realm of politics.

A state of affairs in which all people within a specific society or isolated group have the same status in certain respects, possibly including civil rights, freedom of speech, property rights and equal access to certain social goods and social services. However, it may also include health equality, economic equality and other social securities.
A concept that applies concerns of justice and fairness to social policy.

A form of literature that uses aesthetic and rhythmic qualities of language—such as phonaesthetics, sound symbolism, and metre—to evoke meanings in addition to, or in place of, the prosaic ostensible meaning.
The specific mode of literature represented in performance: a play, opera, mime, ballet, etc., performed in a theatre, or on radio or television.

Any narrative consisting of imaginary people, events, or descriptions—in other words, a narrative not based strictly on history or fact. It also commonly refers, more narrowly, to written narratives in prose and often specifically novels.
A piece of writing that gives the author's own argument — but the definition is vague, overlapping with those of a paper, an article, a pamphlet, and a short story.
A term used in the book-trade for fictional works written with the intent of fitting into a specific literary genre, in order to appeal to readers and fans already familiar with that genre.
Fictions which derive from other fictions, either being directly inspired by or continuations or alternate histories of.

A type of fictional text written by fans of any work of fiction where the author uses established characters, settings, and/or other intellectual properties from an original creator as a basis for their writing.
A prevailing negative reaction towards men who act in a feminine way.
An act thereof can describe as the denial of full humanness to others, and the cruelty and suffering that accompany it.
The process by which a person or group of persons comes to be regarded or treated as lacking in human qualities.
The act of treating a person, or sometimes an animal, as an object or a thing.
The act of treating a person as a mere object of sexual desire.
The process by which someone or something is made the subject of sexual obsession.
A subculture composed of fans characterized by a feeling of empathy and camaraderie with others who share a common interest.
A subculture interested in anthropomorphic animal characters with human personalities and characteristics.
Therapeutic, nutritional, environmental, social and/or behavioral interventions at the societal, community, organizational or individual levels to reduce, modify or stop the course of something.
Preventing or hindering persons or other entities from accessing something, such as particular information or resources.
The controlling of access to health services, usually by primary care providers; often used in managed care settings to reduce utilization of expensive services and reduce referrals.
A business whose primary function is the serving of alcoholic beverages for consumption on the premises.
A business serving mostly LGBTQIA+ persons whose primary function is the serving of alcoholic beverages for consumption on the premises.
Material depicting sexual behavior. The sexual behavior involved may be explicit, implicit sexual behavior such as flirting, or include sexual language and euphemisms.
Any literary or artistic work that deals substantively with subject matter that is erotically stimulating or sexually arousing but is not pornographic.
The portrayal of sexual subject matter for the exclusive purpose of sexual arousal.
Discrete items of erotica; broadly, curiosities which may include erotic or pornographic books or materials.
Erotica and pornography as discrete, collectable items, usually in published or printed form.
Pornography containing LGBTQIA+ content or persons or otherwise pertaining to the LGBTQIA+ community.
Pornography containing lesbian content or lesbians or otherwise pertaining to the lesbian community.
Pornography containing gay male content or gay men or otherwise pertaining to the gay male community.
Pornography containing transgender content or transgender persons or otherwise pertaining to the transgender community.
Pornography containing bisexual content or persons or otherwise pertaining to the bisexual community.
Erotica containing LGBTQIA+ content or persons or otherwise pertaining to the LGBTQIA+ community.
Erotica containing gay male content or gay men or otherwise pertaining to the gay male community.
Erotica containing lesbian content or lesbians or otherwise pertaining to the lesbian community.
Erotica containing transgender content or persons or otherwise pertaining to the transgender community.
Erotica containing bisexual content or persons or otherwise pertaining to the bisexual community.
A business which either directly or indirectly provides sex-related services.

Note that sex work involes the direct efforts involving a worker or workers sexuality, sex appeal, or other sex-based characteristics, while sex services or the sex industry includes not only these, but also indirect efforts such as the producers and directors in pornographic films, manufacturers of sex toys, managers of brothels, escort agents, etc.
The exchange of sexual services, performances, or products for material compensation

Note that sex work involes the direct efforts involving a worker or workers sexuality, sex appeal, or other sex-based characteristics, while sex services or the sex industry includes not only these, but also indirect efforts such as the producers and directors in pornographic films, manufacturers of sex toys, managers of brothels, escort agents, etc.
The business or practice of engaging in sexual activity in exchange for payment.
Prostitution services with a primary purpose being the exchange of sexual intercourse for pay.
Prostitution services without a primary purpose being the exchange of sexual intercourse for pay.

Prostitution and/or sexual slavery that takes place as a result of coercion by a third party. Forced prostitution is a crime against the person because of the violation of the victim's rights of movement through coercion and because of their commercial exploitation.
Sexual rites consisting of sexual intercourse or other sexual activity performed in the context of religious worship, perhaps as a form of fertility rite or divine marriage (hieros gamos).
Some scholars prefer the terms "sacred sex" or "sacred sexual rites" to "sacred prostitution" in cases where payment for services was not involved.
Prostitution involving a child, and it is a form of commercial sexual exploitation of children.
Prostitution involving an adolescent, and it is a form of commercial sexual exploitation of adolescents.
Forced prostitution of individuals under the age of 18.
Types of prostitution organized by the gender of the clients and/or sex workers.
Prostitution in which the sex worker or workers are female.
Prostitution in which the sex worker or workers are male.
